\paragraph*{{\it 4. Closures to the galactic mid-plane}}
It is important that the galaxy is built in different way in different regions in the sky . the shape of galactic stellar distribution is very complex , which reflects the evolution model of galactic disk with several phase transitions and various feedback mechanisms included . the dark matter is less important in building the morphology of stellar distribution than the baryons in the present stage , especially with the weak positive feedback in the small scale . in the simulation , the evolution of dark matter is very slow . compared with the baryons , dark matter can not change the morphology of the stellar distribution very much . the dark halo is a nearly spherical particle distribution , not a massive particle distribution .

